<p>Similarly, WebBlocks also provides a set of classes that allow a user to align text above a breakpoint, whereas at or below the breakpoint, the element will be rendered without the alignment:

<div class="row medium-small-collapse">
    <div class="panel-6">
        <ul class="unstyled list">
            <li><code>.text-left-above-xxsmall</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-xsmall</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-small</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-medium-small</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-medium</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-medium-large</code></li>
            <li><code>.text-left-above-large</code></li>
