        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<p>An element with <code>.text-center-medium</code> will be aligned to the center at or below <code>$breakpoint-medium</code>, whereas an element <code>.text-right-above-medium</code> will be aligned to the right above <code>$breakpoint-medium</code>:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;div class="text-center-medium"&gt;
    &lt;!-- center-aligned at or below medium breakpoint --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="text-right-above-medium"&gt;
    &lt;!-- right-aligned above medium breakpoint --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>

<div class="text-center-medium">
    .text-center-medium
</div>
<div class="text-right-above-medium">
    .text-right-above-medium
</div>

<p>These can be mixed and matched to define alignments besides the container alignment both above and below a breakpoint as follows:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;div class="text-center-medium text-right-above-medium"&gt;
    &lt;!-- center-aligned at or below medium breakpoint, 
          or right-aligned above medium breakpoint --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</pre>

<div class="text-center-medium text-right-above-medium">
    .text-center-medium.text-right-above-medium
</div>

<h3>Font</h3>

<p>This module defines a number of base styles:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Font size and family for the body</li>
    <li>Font sizes, margins, line heights and margins for the header, paragraph and list item tags</li>
    <li>Styling for <code>abbr[title]</code>, <code>address</code>, <code>blockquote</code>, <code>cite</code> and <code>hr</code> tags</li>
</ul>

